## 1. Introduction

### 1.1 Scope

This change request extends the existing modules table in the Code Intelligence SQLite database to store pattern metadata detected during code indexing. The Code Intelligence system currently operates across 6 MCP server variants (Node.js, Python, Kotlin, Bash, PowerShell, CMD) that share a common SQLite schema stored at {workspace}/.code-intel/index.db.

The current modules table stores basic module information (id, name, root\_path, language, file\_count, symbol\_count, last\_indexed) but does not persist the detected coding patterns (DI style, error handling, naming conventions, logging framework, testing framework, module purpose). These patterns are currently computed at runtime but lost between sessions.

This CR adds 6 new columns to the modules table to persist pattern metadata, implements automatic schema migration on server startup, and ensures backward compatibility across all 6 MCP server variants.

### 1.2 Out of Scope

* Changes to the files, symbols, or any other existing tables
* Changes to the pattern detection logic itself (detection algorithms remain unchanged)
* Adding new MCP tools or endpoints
* UI/frontend changes
* Changes to the Knowledge Base ingestion pipeline
* Performance optimization of existing queries
* Adding indexes on the new columns (can be addressed in a future CR if needed)

### 1.3 Preliminary Requirement

* All 6 MCP server variants must be functional and passing tests before migration implementation
* The existing SQLite database schema must be documented and consistent across all variants
* Access to all 6 variant codebases (Node.js, Python, Kotlin, Bash, PowerShell, CMD)

## 2. Business Requirements

### 2.1 High Level Process Map

The schema extension follows a standard database migration pattern applied across multiple language implementations:

flowchart TD
 A[Server Startup] --> B{Check DB exists?}
 B -->|No| C[Create DB with full schema including new columns]
 B -->|Yes| D{Check if new columns exist?}
 D -->|Yes| E[Continue normal operation]
 D -->|No| F[Run ALTER TABLE migration]
 F --> G[Add 6 new columns with NULL defaults]
 G --> E
 E --> H[Index workspace modules]
 H --> I[Detect patterns per module]
 I --> J[Write pattern metadata to modules table]
 J --> K[Serve MCP requests with enriched data]

