## 8. Appendix

### Glossary

|  |  |
| --- | --- |
| Term | Definition |
| MCP | Model Context Protocol — the protocol used by Code Intelligence servers to communicate with AI agents |
| DI Style | Dependency Injection Style — how dependencies are provided to classes (constructor injection, field injection, none) |
| Pattern Metadata | Coding patterns detected by static analysis: DI style, error handling, naming conventions, logging, testing, purpose |
| Schema Migration | The process of updating a database schema to a new version while preserving existing data |
| Variant | One of the 6 language implementations of the Code Intelligence MCP server |

